-- Copperman’s Omega Expands Stake in SPDR Gold ETF, Filing Shows
-- B y   S t e v e   S t r o t h
-- 2012-02-10T18:14:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-10/copperman-s-omega-expands-stake-in-spdr-gold-etf-filing-shows.html
Leon Cooperman ’s Omega Advisors Inc.
increased its stake in the SPDR Gold Trust, an exchange-traded
fund backed by the metal, by 27 percent during the fourth
quarter, according to a regulatory filing.  The New York-based hedge fund added 198,100 shares during
the three months ended Dec. 31, bringing its holding to 919,600,
a filing today with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission
showed. SPDR is the biggest exchange-traded product backed by
gold.  To contact the reporter on this story:
